  "notes": "Kikuyu (Gĩkũyũ), Bantu language of central Kenya. Latin orthography with the tilde vowels ⟨ĩ ũ⟩ for the close-mid /e o/, while plain ⟨e o⟩ are the open-mid /ɛ ɔ/. ⟨b d g⟩ are the fricatives /β ð ɣ/, ⟨c⟩ = /ʃ/, and the prenasalised stops are written ⟨mb nd ng nj⟩; ⟨ng'⟩ is plain /ŋ/. Kikuyu is tonal but tone is not written in the standard orthography and is not modelled here.",
